  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3491" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi> Schuchardt, </opener>

        <p>your card received tonight consoles me a little, especially as it is accompanied by a letter from the President of the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.4686">Société Ramond</ref> promising at last to fulfil their promise to publish my text of the Pastorale de S<hi
            rendition="#sup">e</hi>. Hélène, the task of copying which nearly killed me as M<hi
            rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Thomas knows – Your silence &amp; that of this society and other bascophiles, and the fact that I have been robbed here of some of my Basque books has nearly driven me to suicide. I shall be adressable at Poste Restante, Oporto, till &amp; after the 20<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> I expect to visit there the <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2017">de Vasconcellos</persName> family to which I have introductions from <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2188">Paul Meyer</persName> &amp; D<hi
            rendition="#sup">r</hi>. <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1805">E. Hübner</persName> &amp; yourself. I shall be at Santiago de Compostela for the 25<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi> S<hi rendition="#sup">t</hi> James day. I read all Leizarragas sermons &amp; am reading Vinsons 93.a. which is better. </p>
        <closer>
          <salute/>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>
          </signed>
          <dateline>
            <note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">Randnotiz auf der linken Seite.</note> Coimbra. 10 July 1894.</dateline>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
    </body>
